The paper deals with mechanism design and voting, which are core topics in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of verification oracles and the analysis of approximation ratios suggest a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's emphasis on social welfare and utility maximization aligns with the field of computational economics (cs.EC).
